---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Severance Library | Case Study | Wet Dog Drones"
  description="How Wet Dog Drones saved Fransen Pittman $40,000 at Severance Library by documenting pre-existing road damage before construction began.">

  <section class="bg-slate-900 text-white py-20">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
        <span class="bg-green-600 text-white text-sm font-bold px-3 py-1 rounded">$40,000 SAVED</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6">Severance Library</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-slate-300">Pre-construction documentation that split an $80,000 change order.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-12">
        <div class="bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
          <div class="text-sm text-slate-500">Client</div>
          <div class="font-semibold">Fransen Pittman</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
          <div class="text-sm text-slate-500">Location</div>
          <div class="font-semibold">Severance, Colorado</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
          <div class="text-sm text-slate-500">Service</div>
          <div class="font-semibold">Pre-Construction Documentation</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">The Problem</h2>
      
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-6">
        After construction was complete, the City of Severance came back claiming $80,000 in road damage caused by construction activity. The roads showed cracks, potholes, and deterioration that the city said was new damage from heavy equipment and construction traffic.
      </p>

      <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-6">
        The contractor was facing a massive change order — one of those "your problem, you pay" moments that every contractor dreads. Without proof of what the roads looked like before construction started, they were in a weak negotiating position.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 mt-12">The Solution</h2>
      
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-6">
        Before anyone stepped on site, Wet Dog Drones had documented the existing road conditions with timestamped, georeferenced orthomosaics. Every crack, every pothole, every imperfection — captured and stored with metadata that can't be disputed.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-600 p-6 my-8">
        <blockquote class="text-xl italic text-blue-900">
          "The drone came in, flew the site, and we had documentation showing the roads were already damaged."
        </blockquote>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 mt-12">The Result</h2>
      
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-6">
        Armed with pre-construction documentation showing existing road damage, the contractor negotiated from a position of strength. Instead of paying $80,000, they split the difference.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-xl p-8 text-center my-8">
        <div class="text-5xl font-bold text-green-600 mb-2">$40,000</div>
        <div class="text-green-800 font-semibold">SAVED</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-green-700 mt-2">From an $80,000 change order to a $40,000 settlement</div>
      </div>

      <blockquote class="bg-slate-100 border-l-4 border-slate-600 p-6 my-8 text-xl italic">
        "I was the hero because I saved a big chunk of money. The drone documentation made all the difference."
      </blockquote>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 mt-12">The Lesson</h2>
      
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-6">
        Every project needs baseline documentation before ground is broken. Roads, curbs, landscaping, site conditions — if it's not documented, it doesn't exist in a dispute. For a fraction of the potential change order cost, the contractor had insurance that paid for itself 10x over.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-12 p-6 bg-amber-50 rounded-lg border border-amber-200">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-amber-900 mb-2">Similar Project?</h3>
        <p class="text-amber-800 mb-4">
          If you're starting a construction project, let's document the site conditions before anyone steps on it. The cost is minimal; the protection is invaluable.
        </p>
        <a href="/contact" class="inline-block bg-amber-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-amber-700 transition">
          Get a Quote
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-20 bg-slate-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">More Case Studies</h2>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <a href="/case-studies/clear-creek-schools" class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition">
          <div class="text-green-600 font-bold text-sm mb-2">$400,000 SAVED</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Clear Creek Schools</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600">Interior documentation proved building was empty before construction — GC ate the $400K change order.</p>
        </a>

        <a href="/case-studies/severmore-project" class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition">
          <div class="text-blue-600 font-bold text-sm mb-2">16 MONTHS</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">The $58 Million Project</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600">Bi-weekly progress flights over 16 months, compressed into an 85-second time-lapse.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
